{
  "timestamp": "2026-06-25T16:47:36Z",
  "title": "Forced light theme (no dark mode)",
  "type": "feature",
  "userRequest": "let's keep this separate from codeyam domain; i bought otterpace.com which we can use",
  "description": "Otterpace is a light-only design (cream/coral Palette) but never pinned a color scheme, so on a Dark Mode device system surfaces flipped dark and clashed: the AI-coach API-key SecureField rendered as a black box, the Today/Coach screens went dark, and coach text/input went light-on-light. Fixed by forcing .preferredColorScheme(.light) at the app scene root (App/App.swift) and on ContentView, so the app always renders its light Palette regardless of device appearance. Verified on a Dark-Mode simulator (black field becomes a clean white field; Today and Coach render fully light); all 95 Swift unit tests pass. This change also stands up a TypeScript test harness (vitest) for the previously-untested backend: 50 unit tests covering the Strava + coach Vercel functions (api/_lib/strava.ts helpers and the coach/strava handlers), registers all 17 backend entities in the glossary, and backfills descriptions for 17 older Swift tests, clearing the project pre-existing audit debt so the strict finalize gate passes.",
